\begin_layout Standard
The barometric efficiency, 
\begin_inset Formula $BE$
\end_inset

, is the fraction of the barometer pressure change that will cause drawdown
 in a (semi) confined aquifer.
 The barometer pressure change is partly taken up by the aquifer matrix
 (the loading efficiency 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ensuremath{LE}}$
\end_inset

) while the rest of supported by a change in head (the barometric efficiency
 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ensuremath{BE}}$
\end_inset

).
 The essence is 
\begin_inset Formula $BE+LE=1$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

